# ARTVENDOOR — Landing Page Brand Implementation Guide

## Project Goal
Redesign the current waitlist landing page to fully align with the official Artvendoor brand system.

The page should feel:

- premium
- gallery-clean
- emotionally artistic
- culturally modern
- minimal but expressive
- immersive and visually memorable

The attached crowd-face artwork image MUST be incorporated as a major visual storytelling element.

Preferred direction:
Use the artwork as the **hero background image**, blended with overlays for readability.

---

# 1) Brand Essence
Artvendoor is a digital marketplace and cultural platform for:

- art sales
- artist discovery
- installations
- art supplies
- creative culture

The landing page must communicate:

> “A gateway into the art world.”

This should feel like entering a digital gallery.

---

# 2) Visual Style Direction
## Keywords
- gallery-clean
- curated
- premium
- modern
- warm
- immersive
- editorial
- cultural luxury
- high trust
- artistic

## Avoid
- startup SaaS look
- overly corporate UI
- loud gradients everywhere
- generic stock visuals
- cluttered sections
- neon tech aesthetics

---

# 3) Color Palette
Use ONLY these brand colors.

## Primary Colors
- Terracotta: `#B15A36`
- Clay Grey: `#D57E40`
- Gallery White: `#FFFFFF`
- Charcoal Grey: `#2A2A2A`

## Usage Rules
### Primary CTA
Use **Terracotta** background with white text.

### Secondary Backgrounds
Use:
- Gallery White
- very light warm grey
- soft textured neutral surfaces

### Text
Primary text: Charcoal Grey

### Accent
Clay Grey for:
- hover states
- soft dividers
- icons
- section highlights

---

# 4) Typography
Use **Gilroy** family.

## Hierarchy
- Hero headline: Gilroy Bold
- Subheadline: Gilroy Regular
- Body copy: Gilroy Light

## Fallback
If Gilroy is unavailable:
- Inter
- Manrope
- system sans-serif

## Style Rules
- strong large editorial headlines
- generous line-height
- lots of whitespace
- elegant spacing
- sharp clean text blocks

---

# 5) Hero Section Redesign (MOST IMPORTANT)
Use the attached artwork image of the colorful crowd face as the **main hero background**.

## Implementation Direction
Use:
- full viewport height (`100vh`)
- background-size: cover
- background-position: center
- dark transparent overlay for readability
- subtle blur layer optional
- parallax effect optional
- slow zoom animation optional

## Overlay Recommendation
Use a dark charcoal overlay:
`rgba(42,42,42,0.45)`

This preserves the emotional power of the image while keeping text readable.

## Layout
Centered hero content:
- logo
- headline
- subheadline
- email waitlist field
- CTA button
- launch countdown

---

